OverviewThis position description is subject to change at any time as needed to meet the requirements of the program or company.Provide Web Content Administration and subject matter expertise with the ability to complete small-scale SharePoint development projects for NAVCENT in support of the Maritime Mission. Provide on-site Web Content Management (UNCLASS/SECRET/JWICS), limited SharePoint development expertise and user training support for the Government’s SharePoint Content Management System and Lotus Domino enterprise platform (Collaboration at Sea (CAS). TS/SCI Clearance required.ResponsibilitiesMajor Job Activities: Managing permissions and moving / copying sites;
Reviewing, maintaining, managing, and configuring accounts and sites;
Monitoring trends and reporting to the Government (e.g., site usage and growth, disk space usage and growth);
Developing and implementing pages and sites for all NAVCENT departments;
Performs mapping of information to designated data repositories;
Possess working knowledge of C#, JavaScript and HTML;
Facilitating monthly training sessions to increase command-wide SharePoint adoption and educate users.Material & Equipment Directly Used: Navy classified and unclassified C4ISR computer systems and ONE-NET.Working Environment: Candidate will work primarily in computer facilities at Naval commands in an office or computer equipment room environment. Work outside of normal work week hours will be required to participate in meetings, troubleshooting efforts, and installations or upgrades. Physical Activities: Personnel may be required to stand or sit for prolonged periods of time.  Individual must be able to lift up to 30 lbs. unassisted.
The worker is required to have close visual acuity to perform an activity such as: preparing and analyzing data and figures; viewing a computer terminal; extensive reading; visual inspection of installed computer and network equipment.QualificationsMinimum Qualifications: BS in Information Technology (or equivalent technical degree) or 5+ years technical experience in related discipline required.
IAT Level 2 Certification (Security+, CCNA Security, CySA+, GICSP, GSEC or SSCP) required.
5+ years’ experience with DoD enterprise or Navy networks.
C4I Systems experience: CENTRIXS, CAS, SharePoint.
Active DoD TS-SCI Security Clearance.Experience / Skills: Provide Web Content Administration and subject matter expertise with the ability to complete small-scale SharePoint development projects.
Provide on-site Web Content Management (UNCLASS/SECRET/JWICS), limited SharePoint development expertise and user training support for the Government’s SharePoint Content Management System and Lotus Domino enterprise platform (Collaboration at Sea (CAS)).
Provide troubleshooting for network and operating system issues across multiple platforms.
Must be able to communicate well both orally and in writing.
Must be able to communicate well with senior Navy/DOD officials and technical personnel.
